title: Slow Cooker Chicken Fajita Chili
directions: Combine all of the ingredients except the lime juice and cilantro in the slow cooker, placing the chicken on top. Cook on low for 6-8 hours, or high for 4-6 hours.
In the last 30 minutes of cooking, remove and shred the chicken. Return it to the slow cooker with the lime juice and cilantro, and stir to combine.
Serve with optional toppings as desired.
ingredients: 1 (15-ounce) can reduced-sodium black beans, drained and rinsed
1 (15-ounce) can reduced-sodium pinto beans, drained and rinsed
